 water struggles, the book makes a compelling argument for integrating the study of social movements within critical political economy.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aCapitalism. 0aGlobal Financial Crisis, 2008-2009xInfluence. 0aNeoliberalism. 0aSocial movementszAustraliavCase studies. 0aSocial movementszIrelandvCase studies. 0aSocial movements. 0aWater rightsxPolitical aspects. 0aWater-supplyxPolitical aspects. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Economy.2bisacsh  aIrish water charges.  aLock the Gate.  acapitalocene.  aexpropriation.  afracking.  aglobal financial crisis.  aneoliberalism.  asocial reproduction.  aspatial fix.  awater crisis.1 aMoore, Madelaine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152616599240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526165992423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526165992/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles